<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 10:26AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...SHOWERs WILL AFFECT NORTHERN CHARLOTTE...SOUTHEASTERN
CAMPBELL...EAST CENTRAL PITTSYLVANIA AND NORTHERN HALIFAX COUNTIES...
At 1024 AM EDT, a band of showers with gusty winds was located over
Ridgeway, or near Ingram, moving northeast at 45 mph.
Wind gusts up to 50 mph are possible with this shower.
Locations impacted include...
Halifax...
Brookneal...
Phenix...
Ingram...
Nathalie...
Drakes Branch...
and Cody.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
